{
  "name": "Matrix 2 tone pulse",
  "id": "MJshfus7PS2WfhdEM",
  "sources": {
    "main": "/* a two-tone variation of the original pattern\"Matrix 2d pulse\"\nBaby steps. Changed some variables. \n thanks to Jeff and ScruffyNerf for allowing me to copy and paste\nsome of there code\n   Twilight\n   */ \n  \nw = 8// the width of the 2D matrix\nzigzag = false //straight or zigzag wiring?\nexport function beforeRender(delta) {\n  t1 = time(.04)*PI2\n  t2 = time(.07)*PI2\n  z = 1+ wave(time(.2))*5\n  t3 = time(.1)\n function easeInSine(x){\n  return 1 - cos((x * PI) / 2); \n} \n}\n\n\n \nexport function render(index) {\n  y = (index/3)\n  x = index%z\n  if (zigzag) {\n    x = (y % 2 == 0 ? x : w-1-x)\n  }\n  h =(1+sin(x/w*z + t1) + cos(y/w*z + t2))*.5\n  h=v =h%.999\n  v = v*v*v\n  // Manually \"wrap\" any input hues outside 0..1.\n  //Manually \"wrap\" any input hues outside 0..1.\n  h = h % 1 + (h < 0)\n  \n  // Fade through black for 2 output hues.\n  // Multiply this by existing v values.\n  fadeThroughBlack = triangle(2 * h)\n  \n  // Map a 0..1 hue into 2 ranges, color1 ± width, and it's compliment\n  color1 = 0.3// Yellow (compliment is blue)\n  width = 0.1\n  h = color1 + width * (4 * (h % 0.75) - 1) + (h >= 0.5) / 2\n  \n  hsv(h, 1, v * fadeThroughBlack)%color1\n} "
  },
  "preview": ""
}